## Transformers.js Testing & Build System Exploration Report

Based on my thorough exploration of the Transformers.js library, here's a comprehensive breakdown of the testing framework, build system, and pipeline architecture:

---

### 1. PIPELINE TESTS - STRUCTURE AND EXAMPLES

**Test File Organization:**
- **Main test entry:** `/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775480551711-3lxxf6/tests/pipelines.test.js`
- **Individual pipeline tests:** `/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775480551711-3lxxf6/tests/pipelines/` (27 pipeline test files)

**Pipeline Test Collection Pattern** (from `test_utils.js` lines 121-133):
```javascript
export async function collect_and_execute_pipeline_tests(title) {
  const all_tests = [];
  const pipeline_types = fs.readdirSync(pipelines_dir);
  for (const filename of pipeline_types) {
    const file = path.join(pipelines_dir, filename);
    const items = await import(file);
    all_tests.push(items);
  }
  describe(title, () => all_tests.forEach((test) => test.default()));
}
```

**Standard Pipeline Test Pattern:**
Each pipeline test file exports a default function that describes a test suite:
```javascript
// Example: test_pipelines_text_classification.js
const PIPELINE_ID = "text-classification";

export default () => {
  describe("Text Classification", () => {
    const model_id = "hf-internal-testing/tiny-random-BertForSequenceClassification";

    let pipe;
    beforeAll(async () => {
      pipe = await pipeline(PIPELINE_ID, model_id, DEFAULT_MODEL_OPTIONS);
    }, MAX_MODEL_LOAD_TIME);

    it("should be an instance of TextClassificationPipeline", () => {
      expect(pipe).toBeInstanceOf(TextClassificationPipeline);
    });

    // Tests organized by batch_size (batch_size=1, batch_size>1)
  });
};
```

---

### 2. IMAGE-TO-TEXT PIPELINE TESTS (MULTIMODAL)

**File:** `/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775480551711-3lxxf6/tests/pipelines/test_pipelines_image_to_text.js`

**Key Details:**
- Task ID: `"image-to-text"` (line 6)
- Uses model: `hf-internal-testing/tiny-random-VisionEncoderDecoderModel-vit-gpt2`
- Type: multimodal (combines images + text tokenizer)

**Test Structure** (lines 8-51):
```javascript
