    }

    /** @type {ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback} */
    async _call(images, texts, generate_kwargs = {}) {

        const isBatched = Array.isArray(images);
        const preparedImages = await prepareImages(images);

        if (!Array.isArray(texts)) {
            texts = [texts];
        }

        const toReturn = [];
        for (let i = 0; i < preparedImages.length; ++i) {
            const inputs = await this.processor(preparedImages[i], texts[i]);
            const output = await this.model.generate({ ...inputs, ...generate_kwargs });
            const decoded = this.tokenizer.batch_decode(/** @type {Tensor} */(output), {
                skip_special_tokens: true,
            }).map(x => ({ generated_text: x.trim() }));
            toReturn.push(decoded);
        }

        return isBatched ? toReturn : toReturn[0];
    }
}
```

**Design notes:**
- Processes each (image, text) pair individually (same approach as `ImageToTextPipeline` which loops over each image) to avoid batching complexity across models with different input shapes.
- `this.processor(image, text)` calls the model-specific processor (e.g. `LlavaProcessor._call(images, text)`) which returns `{ pixel_values, input_ids, attention_mask }`.
- `{ ...inputs, ...generate_kwargs }` spreads all processor outputs into `model.generate()`. The `_prepare_model_inputs` method (models.js line 1616) picks only `forward_params`-declared keys, so extra keys are safely ignored.
- `this.tokenizer.batch_decode` uses the standalone tokenizer for decoding (same pattern as `ImageToTextPipeline`).

